{# Default preamble written into the manifest repo by
   `gasp manifest init`. Variables:
     name (str) — workspace display name. #}
# {{ name }} workspace — agent preamble

This text is prepended to the workspace's aggregated agent context
file by `gasp context sync`. Edit it with workspace-level instructions
that should always be in scope.

Things worth putting here:

- Conventions that span multiple repos (style, testing approach,
  release process).
- Pointers to where canonical decisions live (e.g. "ADRs are in
  `architecture/`; check there before proposing a new approach").
- House rules for agents (what to ask vs. just do, how to format
  commits, etc.).

Things that belong in per-repo `CLAUDE.md` files instead:

- Repo-specific tooling, build commands, and code conventions —
  agents pick those up automatically when working inside the repo.

This file lives in the manifest repo and is version-controlled
alongside `workspace.toml`. Edit it freely; `gasp context sync`
never overwrites it.
